00:00:30.120 --> 00:00:33.810
but it's especially important when you're working on a coding project.

00:00:33.810 --> 00:00:36.990
One of the key aspects of collaboration is being able to communicate

00:00:36.990 --> 00:00:40.277
clearly what you're doing and being able to work with others,

00:00:40.277 --> 00:00:41.774
like the project's maintainers,

00:00:41.774 --> 00:00:43.969
to see how you can contribute.

00:00:43.969 --> 00:00:48.844
This communication can be kind of tricky when working remotely and asynchronously.

00:00:48.844 --> 00:00:49.993
After going through this course,

00:00:49.993 --> 00:00:53.144
you'll be able to work with others on a version control project,

00:00:53.145 --> 00:00:58.289
use GitHub and its features to plan changes and implement those changes,

00:00:58.289 --> 00:01:00.719
contribute to an existing repository,

00:01:00.719 --> 00:01:04.867
and then how to add features to a project while it's in active development.

00:01:04.867 --> 00:01:06.030
And if you're taking this course,

00:01:06.030 --> 00:01:07.709
